<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF736ACCF7EA952917FEBE8B" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF736ACCF7EA952917FEBE8B" blockId="136.[2069,2663,800,1228]" lastBlockId="136.[1457,2666,1235,3201]" pageId="136" pageNumber="896">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF7EA9529172CB8A3" authorityName="Horsfield" authorityYear="1824" box="[2070,2348,880,913]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hardwickii">Kerwoula hardwickii</taxonomicName>
previously included populations now attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF63395CE145FB88A" authorityName="G. S. Miller" authorityYear="1906" box="[2511,2655,919,952]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="depressa">K. depressa</taxonomicName>
, K. malpasi, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF74E95E71728B8ED" authorityName="Wroughton &amp; Ryley" authorityYear="1913" box="[2226,2344,958,991]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crypta">K. crypta</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF6C595E717A7B8ED" box="[2361,2471,958,991]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="furva">K. furva</taxonomicName>
, and K. dongduongana from throughout South Asia and 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF736ACCF7EB925416A4BF1C" box="[2071,2212,1037,1070]" country="Botswana" name="South East" pageId="136" pageNumber="896">South-east</collectingRegion>
Asia. These species, along with 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF7EA926016D1BF64" box="[2070,2257,1081,1110]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kachinensis">K. kachinensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF71992601787BF64" box="[2277,2439,1081,1110]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="krauensis">K. krauensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF6609260141CBF64" box="[2460,2588,1081,1110]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="titania">K. titania</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF7EA9205169DBF4F" authorityName="G. S. Miller" authorityYear="1898" box="[2070,2205,1116,1149]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minuta">K. minuta</taxonomicName>
, comprise the 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF685920517FABF4F" authorityName="Horsfield" authorityYear="1824" box="[2425,2554,1116,1149]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hardwickii">hardwickii</taxonomicName>
species group, with 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF73992DD1743BF97" box="[2245,2371,1156,1189]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="titania">K. titania</taxonomicName>
occupying the most basal position in the clade. Genetic data places K. hardwickuisister to K.© ahi Genetic and morphological data support recognition of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF9CA92A318C2BE29" authorityName="G. S. Miller" authorityYear="1906" box="[1590,1730,1274,1307]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="depressa">K. depressa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF92F92A31941BE29" box="[1747,1857,1274,1307]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="furva">K. furva</taxonomicName>
, and K. dongduongana as distinct species, and limited biogeographical data support recognition of K. erypta and K. malpasi (although they might be conspecific). Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF89793101614BE58" authorityName="Horsfield" authorityYear="1824" box="[1899,2068,1353,1386]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hardwickii">K. hardwickii</taxonomicName>
is ends in 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF736ACCF75993101733BE58" box="[2213,2355,1353,1386]" country="Botswana" name="South East" pageId="136" pageNumber="896">South-east</collectingRegion>
Asia at ¢.16” N, which leaves it allopatric with 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF90793281969BEA0" box="[1787,1897,1393,1426]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="furva">K. furva</taxonomicName>
. Additional studies are needed to further differentiate species in the 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF736ACCF98993C118F6BE8B" authorityName="Horsfield" authorityYear="1824" box="[1653,1782,1432,1465]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="896" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hardwickii">hardwickii</taxonomicName>
group with genetic and morphological data. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
